## Key Findings from Analysis

- CDK6 (not CDK4) is primary CDKN2A-selective dependency — ROBUST in 6 cancer types
- WDR77/PRMT5 methylosome axis is top novel pan-cancer hit (d=-0.581), but possibly MTAP co-deletion driven
- Trilaciclib (CDK4/6i) confirms selectivity in PRISM (d=-0.539)
- RB1 co-loss abolishes CDK6 dependency (negative control validated)
- ~125,815 CDKN2A-del patients/yr US; priority: Bladder, Mesothelioma, Ovary, Skin
- Success criterion 2 (novel non-CDK4/6 in >=2 types) partially met — validation scientist must rule

